if;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">231</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":231,\"repo\":\"irazasyed/awesome-cloudflare\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - CDN, DNS, DDoS protection, and security for your site.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-03T14:14:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caesar0301/awesome-pcaptools","categoryHTML":"<h2>Traffic Analysis/Inspection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/simsong/tcpflow\">Tcpflow</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/simsong/tcpflow\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1249,\"repo\":\"simsong/tcpflow\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->: A program that captures data transmitted as part of TCP connections (flows), and stores the data in a way that is convenient for protocol analysis or debugging. A program like 'tcpdump' shows a summary of packets seen on the wire, but usually doesn't store the data that's actually being transmitted. In contrast, tcpflow reconstructs the actual data streams and stores each flow in a separate file for later analysis. Yet, optionally, it can isolate pcap flows per tcp flow for granularized inspection. <a href=\"http://www.circlemud.org/jelson/software/tcpflow/\">Original link</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-03T14:00:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"joaomilho/awesome-idris","categoryHTML":"<h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/gidti\">Gentle Introduction to Dependent Types with Idris</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-03T11:08:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h6>Other</h6>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/meetfranz/franz\">Franz</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/meetfranz/franz\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3972,\"repo\":\"meetfranz/franz\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Skype, Slack, Hangouts, WhatsApp, Grape, Telegram, FB Messenger, Hipchat in the same app.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-03T10:49:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hackerkid/bots","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platform Documentation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/hangouts/chat/concepts/\">Hangouts Chat</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-03T08:37:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Energy</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://openclimatefix.github.io\">Open Climate Fix</a> | London, England | 2019</p>\n<p>Non-profit research and development lab, focused on reducing greenhouse gas emissions by solving machine learning problems. As of 2019 they are working on a forecasting system to reduce gas turbines backups on power grids that use solar energy.</p>